description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deepdene Care is a national mental healthcare provider operating five homes nationwide, offering high quality care to people with severe and enduring mental health needs. It was established in 1987, providing services that include specialised nursing and residential care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have some exciting opportunities and are looking for reliable, experienced individuals with a friendly and caring nature to work as a registered nurse in &lt;strong&gt;Littlehampton, West Sussex , BN17 5HS.&lt;/strong&gt; In-house training is provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time Hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£3,000 joining fee&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A responsible and caring attitude is important. You will work in friendly but sometimes challenging environments, therefore excellent interaction and communication skills are essential. Your role will involve planning, assessing and evaluating Care Plans and Risk Assessments, preparing for attending team meetings and other appropriate multi-professional meetings. To maintain and keep updated on new clinical and nursingdevelopments. Whilst ensuring a high standard of nursing in the application of clinical nursing procedures and treatments including the custody, storage and administration of drugs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful applicants are required to provide an enhanced disclosure.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We can offer successful applicants benefits such as:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·An opportunity to work for a company who invest in their employees and have recently celebrated 30 years of success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·Pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.Free DBS check&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·In-house Training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Deepdene Contract of Employment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Employee Assistance Programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·Excellent overtime opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this appeals to you, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please ensure you complete the application form in full. Partially complete forms will not be accepted.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to withdraw the vacancy at any time If there is a high volume of applications, therefore we would recommend that you submit your application as early as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
